description: Log of COTS population growth rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_cots ≈ 2.0, representing potential for rapid population growth during outbreaks.
Log of COTS carrying capacity (individuals/m²). Corresponds to K_cots ≈ 2.0, representing maximum sustainable density.
Log of temperature effect on COTS reproduction (dimensionless). Controls steepness of temperature response curve.
Log of temperature threshold for COTS reproduction (°C). Corresponds to ~28°C, above which COTS reproduction increases.
Log of effect of larval immigration on COTS recruitment (dimensionless). Scales the impact of external larval supply.
Log of intrinsic growth rate of fast-growing coral (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_fast ≈ 0.5, representing annual growth rate of Acropora spp.
Log of intrinsic growth rate of slow-growing coral (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_slow ≈ 0.2, representing annual growth rate of Faviidae and Porites spp.
Log of carrying capacity of fast-growing coral (%). Corresponds to K_fast ≈ 50%, maximum potential cover for Acropora spp.
Log of carrying capacity of slow-growing coral (%). Corresponds to K_slow ≈ 40%, maximum potential cover for slow-growing species.
Log of attack rate on fast-growing coral (m²/individual/year). Corresponds to a_fast ≈ 0.1, representing COTS preference for Acropora spp.
Log of attack rate on slow-growing coral (m²/individual/year). Corresponds to a_slow ≈ 0.05, representing lower COTS preference for slow-growing species.
Log of handling time for fast-growing coral (year/%). Corresponds to h_fast ≈ 0.01, time spent consuming Acropora spp.
Log of handling time for slow-growing coral (year/%). Corresponds to h_slow ≈ 0.02, longer time spent consuming tougher slow-growing species.
Log of coral cover effect on COTS survival (dimensionless). Corresponds to coral_effect ≈ 10, half-saturation constant for coral-dependent survival.
Log of observation error SD for COTS. Corresponds to sigma_cots ≈ 0.2, representing measurement error in COTS surveys.
Log of observation error SD for fast-growing coral. Corresponds to sigma_fast ≈ 0.5, representing measurement error in coral cover surveys.
Log of observation error SD for slow-growing coral. Corresponds to sigma_slow ≈ 0.5, representing measurement error in coral cover surveys.
